Abstract: The bride is a fund-raising manager at Teach for America; the bridegroom is a lawyer.
Snippet: The bride is a fund-raising manager at Teach for America; the bridegroom is a lawyer.
LeadParagraph: Callan Marie Blount, a daughter of Phyllis Bisch Marwill and Sherwood E. Blount Jr., both of Dallas, was married Friday evening in Brooklyn to Benjamin Andrew Fleming, a son of Ruth Levy Fleming and Robert B. Fleming Jr. of Buffalo. Blair A. Heiser, who introduced the couple and who became an American Marriage Ministries minister for the event, officiated at the Old Stone House, a museum.
